[3] Israel (Immigrants)
Date: 9 May 2012
Source: Arutz Sheva [edited]
http://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/Flash.aspx/239403#.T6_dSe2aCQg


Measles Outbreak Among Foreign Job-Seekers
---------------------------------------
Several cases of measles have been reported among foreign job-seekers and their children since January [2012], the Health Ministry reported Wednesday [9 May 2012]. Seven foreign citizens living in Tel Aviv were diagnosed with measles in the past week, 6 of them babies who required hospital care.

The Ministry has begun a campaign to vaccinate the young children of foreign job-seekers and their parents. Babies as young as 6 months will be given the vaccine in hopes of preventing the spread of the illness.

--
